# $Id$
#
# Group membership checking
#

Module depends on: a database module

This module export functions necesarry for group membership
checking. There is a database table that contains list of users and
groups they belong to. The table is used by functions of this module.

Exported Parameters:
-------------------

Name:    db_url
Type:    str
Default: "sql://serro:47serro11@localhost/ser"
Desc:    URL of the database table to be used

Name:    table
Type:    str
Default: "grp"
Desc:    Name of the table holding groups and their members

Name:    user_column
Type:    str
Default: "username"
Desc:    Name of the column holding usernamens

Name:    domain_column
Type:    str
Default: "domain"
Desc:    Name of the column holding domains

Name:    group_column
Type:    str
Default: "grp"
Desc:    Name of the column holding groups

Name:    use_domain
Type:    int
Default: 0 (no)
Desc:    If set to 1 then username@domain will be
         used for lookup, if set to 0 then only
	 username will be used


Exported Functions:
------------------

Name:   is_user_in
Params: URI - URI whose username and optionally domain to be
              used, this can be one of:
	      Request-URI -- use Request-URI username and domain
	      To -- Use To username and domain
	      From -- Use From username and domain
	      Credentials -- Use digest credentials username
	group - Name of the group to check
Desc:   The function returns true if username in the given URI is
        member of the given group and false if not.
